data.name: RESPONSE MODEL /domains
spam_action
data.description: One of: "Disable","Tag". Disable, no spam filtering will occur for inbound messages. Tag, messages will be tagged wtih a spam header

data.name: wildcard
data.description: One of "true" or "false" . Determines whether the domain will accept email for sub-domains.

data.name: password
data.description: A password for the SMTP credentials. (Length Min 5, Max 32)

data.name: domain
data.description: Name of domain to be deleted

data.name: domain
data.description: The site whose credentials you want to retrieve
Retrieve only information linked to yourdomain.com
data.name: Information about "yourdomain.com"
limit
data.description: Maximum number of records to return. (100 by default)

data.name: skip
data.description: Number of records to skip. (0 by default)
Retrieve information regarding associated domains with your account

response.name: RESPONSE MODEL /domains

data.name: Information for all domains
domain
data.description: The hostname of your site as specified in the control panel

data.name: attachment
data.description: File attachment. You can post multiple attachment values. Important: You must use multipart/form-data encoding when sending attachments.

data.name: bcc
data.description: Same as To but for Bcc

data.name: cc
data.description: Same as To but for Cc

data.name: inline
data.description: Attachment with inline disposition. Can be used to send inline images (see example). You can post multiple inline values.

data.name: o:campaign
data.description: Id of the campaign the message belongs to

data.name: o:deliverytime
data.description: Desired time of delivery; max 3 days

data.name: o:dkim
data.description: One of "Yes", "No" to enable or disable DKIM signature on messages sent

data.name: o:tag
data.description: Sometimes its helpful to categorize your outgoing email traffic based on some criteria. Mailgun lets you tag each outgoing message with a custom value. When you access stats on you messages, they will be aggregated by these tags.

data.name: to
data.description: Email address of the recipient(s). Example: "Bob <bob@host.com>". You can use commas to separate multiple recipients.

description: Mailgun is a programmable email platform. It allows your application to become a fully featured email server. Send, receive and track messages with ease using your favorite programming language.
name: v1
